<worksheet xml:id="wksht-plotting_points_in_the_plane" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" component="notes">
  <title>Plotting Points in the Plane</title>
  <objectives>
    <ul>
      <li>
	<p>
	  Plot points in the plane using Cartesian coordinates,
	</p>
      </li>
      <li>
	<p>
	  Identify the quadrant in which a point lies.
	</p>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </objectives>
  <introduction>
    <p>
      In this activity, we will practice plotting some points in the plane.
    </p>
  </introduction>
  <page>
    <exercise workspace=".5in">
      <statement>
	<p>Plot the following points in the Cartesian plane.</p>
	<figure>
	  <image width="50%">
	    <latex-image >
	      <xi:include parse="text" href="../tex/10_10_grid.tex" />
	    </latex-image>
	  </image>
	</figure>
	<sidebyside widths="20% 40% 25%" margins="auto" valign="middle">
	  <p><m>A = (-1,3)</m></p>
	  <p><m>B = (-2,-1)</m></p>
	  <p><m>C = (3,5.5)</m></p>
	</sidebyside>
	<sidebyside widths="20% 40% 25%" margins="auto" valign="middle">
	  <p><m>D = (3,-4)</m></p>
	  <p><m>E = (-8,-2)</m></p>
	  <p><m>F = (5.5,3)</m></p>
	</sidebyside>
      </statement>
    </exercise>
    <exercise workspace=".5in">
      <statement>
	<p>
